The basic class assigned to all characters. You will be able to change your job once you enter the game world.

Humans in Xenomech are versatile and adaptive, embodying the essence of survival and ingenuity amidst the challenges of Arcanis. As one of the most populous and diverse races, Humans thrive in various roles, from scholars and explorers to warriors and innovators. Their natural resilience, ambition, and resourcefulness make them a cornerstone in the factional power struggles and Ether-fueled advancements that define the world.
Alignments are not in use on this server. Please click OK to continue.

Your character is guided by six core attributes: Might, Vitality, Perception, Willpower, Agility, and Social.

Might: Improves damage dealt by melee weapons and increases carrying capacity.
Vitality: Improves your max hit points (HP) and reduces damage received.
Perception: Improves damage dealt by ranged and finesse weapons and increases physical accuracy.
Willpower: Improves your ether attack, ether defense, and max ether points (EP).
Agility: Improves ranged accuracy, evasion, and critical hits.
Social: Improves your XP gain and leadership capabilities.

Might improves damage dealt by melee weapons and increases carrying capacity.

Accuracy: This property grants an enhancement bonus to attack rolls made with the weapon, but does not improve the damage dealt by the weapon on a successful hit.

Accuracy vs. Monster Type: This property grants an enhancement bonus to attack rolls made with the weapon, but does not improve the damage dealt by the weapon on a successful hit. It grants this bonus only against a specific monster type, such as giants, undead, or shapeshifters.

Accuracy vs. Specific Alignment: This property grants an enhancement bonus to attack rolls made with the weapon, but does not improve the damage dealt by the weapon on a successful hit. It grants this bonus only when used against creatures of a specific alignment, such as chaotic neutral, lawful evil, or neutral good.

Accuracy vs. Alignment Group: This property grants an enhancement bonus to attack rolls made with the weapon, but does not improve the damage dealt by the weapon on a successful hit. It grants this bonus only when used against creatures from a specific alignment group, such as evil or lawful creatures.
Accuracy Penalty: This property inflicts a penalty on the wielder's attack rolls made with the weapon.
Accuracy Penalty: This property inflicts a penalty on the wielder's attack and damage rolls made with the weapon.

Summoners who bond with Etheric creatures, commanding pets to assist in combat while thriving in various environments.
Close-range melee fighters who channel Ether into powerful hand-to-hand techniques, executing rapid combos and explosive strikes.
Spellcasters who manipulate elemental forces such as fire, ice, and lightning to unleash devastating Ether-based attacks.
Ranged combatants adept at tracking, scouting, and executing precision attacks with bows or crossbows.
Defensive specialists who absorb damage, control enemies, and protect allies using Ether-powered barriers and crowd control abilities.
Skilled healers who restore health, cleanse ailments, and enhance team survivability with Ether-driven healing arts.
Stealthy assassins who master ambush tactics, Ether-infused concealment, and precision strikes to eliminate key targets.
Tactical controllers who blend Ether and technology to manipulate perception, disrupt enemies, and alter battlefield dynamics.

In Xenomech, the job system represents how individuals harness Ether, technology, and combat expertise to survive on Arcanis. Each job defines a specialized role, from melee combatants to Etheric spellcasters, shaped by Resonance Nodes that allow blending of abilities.

Players start with a primary job and can switch at Zenithias Resonance Chamber, adapting their skills to new challenges. Jobs align with key combat stylesdefensive, support, melee, ranged, or spellcastingoffering deep customization and synergy.
